{
    "description_long": "This object consists of a group of five distinct grave markers, each made from gray stone and varying in shape and size. Four of the markers are simple headstones with rounded or irregular tops, while the fifth features a prominent brown cross mounted on a taller, angular stone base. The surfaces of the stones are rough and weathered, with visible engravings of 'R.I.P.' on several of the markers. The cross is a classic Latin style, contrasting with the otherwise monochrome gray stones. The arrangement suggests a small section of a graveyard, with each marker representing an individual grave. The overall appearance is somber and utilitarian, suitable for a cemetery or memorial setting.",
